        {% if request.user.is_authenticated %}

          <!-- If user is uthenticated -->
          <li class="nav-item">
            <a class="nav-link" href="#" data-toggle="modal" data-target="#instructions">
            Instructions for Admin <span class="sr-only">(current)</span>
            </a>

            <!-- Modal -->
            <div class="modal fade bd-example-modal-lg" id="instructions" tabindex="-1" role="dialog" aria-labelledby="myLargeModalLabel" aria-hidden="true">
              <div class="modal-dialog modal-lg">
                <div class="modal-content">
 
                  <div class="modal-header">
                    <h5 class="modal-title w-100 text-center" id="exampleModalLabel"> <i class="fa fa-info" aria-hidden="true"></i>  Adding Books</h5>
                    <button type="button" class="close" data-dismiss="modal" aria-label="Close">
                      <span aria-hidden="true">&times;</span>
                    </button>
                  </div>
                  <div class="modal-body" style="border-bottom:none;">
                    <ul style="list-style-type: disc;" class="instructions">
                      <li style="margin-bottom:1.2rem;">
                        <p class="instruction-list" style="font-size: 0.8rem;">
                          Login to your account using the given id and pasword for your admin account. As you will login, you can see
                          the groups and users which admin can add more depending upon the required task. The list of books and pages
                          is also visible. Under the Recent Actions tab you can see what changes have been made to the list of the
                          recent books whether added, removed or edited the details within them.
                        </p>
                          <img src="media/images/instr/1.png" alt="2" class="modal-img-cont" style="max-width: 90%;display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;">
                      </li>
                      <li style="margin-bottom:1.2rem;">
                        <p class="instruction-list" style="font-size: 0.8rem;">
                          Click on the Books under Home tab and this page will pop up. Youcan see the already added books and can delete
                          them using the Actions dropdown. The Add Book option on the rightmost top will help in adding more books to your
                          list.
                        </p>
                          <img src="media/images/instr/2.png" alt="3" class="modal-img-cont" style="max-width: 90%;display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;">
                      </li>
                      <li style="margin-bottom:1.2rem;">
                        <p class="instruction-list" style="font-size: 0.8rem;">
                          While adding, the bold attributes are required to be added for a particluar book. Add the title, number of pages,
                          ISBN, etc and other metadata in the emty fields. For adding the values to the book content and book pdf field , 
                          make sure the book you are adding has two compressed folders inside it. Ex. If the book name is Nursery Rhymes,
                          the main folder should contain the nursery_rhymes_imgs.zip and nursery_rhymes_txt.zip inside it.
                          <br>
                          The following should be the model tree :
                          <br>
                          <img src="media/images/instr/6.png" alt="4" class="modal-img-cont" style="max-width: 40%;display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;margin-bottom:0.8rem;">
                          <i style="color:red;">Remember that the number of the images and text files in both the folder should be the same.
                          Apart from that the image files should be of .jpg format and the text should be of .jpg.txt format.</i> It is easier
                          that way to update the searchengine data.
                        </p>
                          <img src="media/images/instr/3.png" alt="4" class="modal-img-cont" style="max-width: 90%;display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;">
                      </li>
                      <li>
                        <p class="instruction-list" style="font-size: 0.8rem;">
                          You can save and can go back to the main admin page where in the book tab, updated book can be viewed. After that,
                          to check whether the page content have been added or not, go to the Pages section under the Home tab and the added
                          pages can be viewed. 
                        </p>
                          <img src="media/images/instr/5.png" alt="3" class="modal-img-cont" style="max-width: 90%;display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;">
                      </li>
                    </ul>
                  </div>
                  <div class="modal-footer text-center">
                    <button type="button" class="btn btn-secondary" data-dismiss="modal">Ok</button>
                    
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </li>


        {% else %}


        <!-- Help -->
        <li class="nav-item">
          <a class="nav-link" href="#" data-toggle="modal" data-target="#help">
            Help<span class="sr-only">(current)</span>
          </a>

          <!-- Modal -->

            <div class="modal fade bd-example-modal-lg" id="help" tabindex="-1" role="dialog" aria-labelledby="myLargeModalLabel" aria-hidden="true">
              <div class="modal-dialog modal-lg" role="document">
                <div class="modal-content" style="border-bottom:none;">
                  <div class="modal-header" style="border-bottom:none;">
                    <h5 class="modal-title w-100 text-center" id="exampleModalLabel"> <i class="fa fa-question" aria-hidden="true" style="margin-right:1rem;"></i> Usage</h5>
                    <button type="button" class="close" data-dismiss="modal" aria-label="Close">
                      <span aria-hidden="true">&times;</span>
                    </button>
                  </div>
                  <div class="modal-body" style="border-bottom:none;">
                    <ul style="list-style-type: disc;" class="help">
                      <li style="margin-bottom:1.2rem;">
                        <p class="help-list" style="font-size: 0.8rem;">
                          Choose the desired language from the dropdown menu and type in the desired
                          query in the search bar provided. This search engine by default searches in English
                          language. After choosing the language, type your query. At the end of the query
                          <i style="color:red;">"DO NOT FORGET TO GIVE A SPACE" </i>  in order to let the 
                          language toggle properly.
                          <br>
                          [Credits : <a href="https://developers.google.com/transliterate/v1/getting_started">
                          Google Transliteration API</a> for open source developers.]
                        </p>
                          <img src="media/images/2.png" alt="2" class="modal-img-cont" style="max-width: 90%;display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;">
                      </li>
                      <li style="margin-bottom:1.2rem;">
                        <p class="help-list" style="font-size: 0.8rem;">
                          Choose the search type/filter from the dropdown menu. Currently available search
                          filters are ISBN based, Title of the books, their author and their content based.
                          This search engine by default searches on the basis of the title of the book 
                          as it is associated with the OCRWeb portal by CVIT,IIITH. After choosing the filter,
                          proceed to search and click on the search button to view results.
                        </p>
                          <img src="media/images/3.png" alt="3" class="modal-img-cont" style="max-width: 90%;display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;">
                      </li>
                      <li>
                        <p class="help-list" style="font-size: 0.8rem;">
                          Finally you can view the results ofthe searched query. Here for example, the user
                          search <i style="color:red;">Munshi Prem Chand</i> in the search bar and language 
                          was chosen as English and filter as Author. The available books in the database
                          were only <i style="color:red;">Godan</i>.Therefore, the results were for Godan. 
                          User can download and read complete book by clicking on <i style="color:red;">Read
                          More</i> link in the abstract of the book. One thing which can be future work is 
                          word spotting amongst the pages of the generated results in certain book.
                        </p>
                          <img src="media/images/4.png" alt="4" class="modal-img-cont" style="max-width: 90%;display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;">
                      </li>
                    </ul>
                  </div>
                  <div class="modal-footer">
                    <button type="button" class="btn btn-secondary" data-dismiss="modal">Close</button>
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>

        </li>

