          <!-- Modal1 -->

          <div class="modal fade" id="disclaimer" tabindex="-1" role="dialog" aria-labelledby="exampleModalLabel" aria-hidden="true">
              <div class="modal-dialog" role="document">
                <div class="modal-content" style="border-bottom:none;">
                  <div class="modal-header" style="border-bottom:none;">
                    <h5 class="modal-title w-100 text-center" id="exampleModalLabel"> <i class="fa fa-exclamation-triangle" aria-hidden="true"></i> Disclaimer</h5>
                    <button type="button" class="close" data-dismiss="modal" aria-label="Close">
                      <span aria-hidden="true">&times;</span>
                    </button>
                  </div>
                  <div class="modal-body" style="border-bottom:none;">
                    
                    <p class="help-list" style="font-size: 0.8rem;">

                      CVITSearch is an amalgamation of contributions made by British Library and IIITH Library
                      in terms of Indic Scripts. Almost all these contents are taken from reliable websites and 
                      books. The responsibility for authenticity, relevance, completeness, accuracy, reliability
                      and suitability of these contents rests with respective organization from where the contents
                      are sourced from and CVITSearch takes no responsibility for these. Efforts are being made to
                      keep this search portal working smoothly and without any interruptions. However, if there are
                      any technical issues, they will be resolved soon. This portal is still under development hence
                      if there are user issues they will be taken care of with time.

                    </p>
                          
                  </div>
                  <div class="modal-footer">
                    <button type="button" class="btn btn-secondary" data-dismiss="modal">Close</button>
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>

            <!-- Modal2 -->



            <div class="modal fade" id="about" tabindex="-1" role="dialog" aria-labelledby="exampleModalLabel" aria-hidden="true">
              <div class="modal-dialog" role="document">
                <div class="modal-content" style="border-bottom:none;">
                  <div class="modal-header" style="border-bottom:none;">
                    <h5 class="modal-title w-100 text-center" id="exampleModalLabel"> <i class="fa fa-info" aria-hidden="true"></i>  About CVITSearch</h5>
                    <button type="button" class="close" data-dismiss="modal" aria-label="Close">
                      <span aria-hidden="true">&times;</span>
                    </button>
                  </div>
                  <div class="modal-body" style="border-bottom:none;">

                    
                    <p class="help-list" style="font-size: 0.8rem;">

                      CVIT,IIITH has initiated this Digital Library of India to develop a framework which encompasses
                      learning resources in Indic Scripts with searching facility, as an academic research project.
                      The design of the platform is such that these learning resources can easily be found out by the
                      users with minimum efforts and time. Currently the search is based in 5 different Indian languages
                      It is being arranged to provide support for all academic levels including researchers and life-long
                      learners, all disciplines, all popular form of access devices. It is an extension of OCRWeb project
                      by CVIT which takes printed Indic Script documents and processes them for character recoginition. 
                      It is being developed to enable people to learn and prepare from best practices from all over the 
                      world and to facilitate researchers to perform inter-linked exploration from multiple sources. 
                      The pilot project is devising a framework that is being scaled up with respect to content volume 
                      and diversity to serve all levels and disciplines of learners. It is being developed at Center for
                      Visual Information and Technology, International Institute of Information and Technology Hyderabad
                      and is being supported by British Library and IIITH Library currently.                      
                    </p>
                          
                  </div>
                  <div class="modal-footer">
                    <button type="button" class="btn btn-secondary" data-dismiss="modal">Close</button>
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>





        </li>


        {% endif %}

      
